&lt;li&gt;Own all benefits programs — health, dental, vision, 401(k), leave, and wellness — from administration to compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for employees navigating benefits questions and open enrollment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage vendor relationships (Sequoia, MetLife, Anthem, Empower) and hold partners accountable to SLAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer multi-state leave programs, ensuring compliance across all jurisdictions where we operate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Finance on audits, 5500 filings, and benefits-related reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support new hire onboarding by educating team members on plan options and enrollment processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead open enrollment each year — planning, communications, and execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive wellness initiatives as we move toward a self-insured model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Match&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of benefits administration experience, ideally at a growing company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with level-funded or self-insured health plans — this is a must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multi-state leave administration experience (FMLA, state-specific leave laws, etc.) — also a must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong vendor management skills and comfort holding brokers and carriers accountable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Rippling or similar HRIS platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with strong attention to detail — you catch what others miss&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
